Machakos woman representative candidate Rita Ndunge has condemned intimidation of non-Wiper contestants in the Ukambani region.Ndunge (pictured) on Saturday accused some Wiper candidates of resorting to intimidation and hooliganism against their opponents &ldquo;after sensing defeat ahead of the August 8 election&rdquo;.&ldquo;I&rsquo;m a courageous independent woman representative candidate in Machakos,&rdquo; she said.Ndunge was addressing the press in Mlolongo town after she was booed by a rowdy crowd, which she said was receptive and &ldquo;cheered me&rdquo;.&ldquo;Apparently, I managed to talk to the locals at the function due to public demand &mdash; nobody booed me,&rdquo; she said, dismissing claims she was booed. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m appealing to residents to support my candidature. My opponents should desist from inciting the public against me by claiming I&rsquo;m Wiper&rsquo;s enemy,&rdquo; she said.Election guidelines require that all candidates be given equal opportunities to campaign and woo voters.